Selenium Interview Questions & Answers – C#
1. Wait Types and Syntax
Implicit Wait: Waits globally for elements.
 Syntax:
driver.Manage().Timeouts().ImplicitWait = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(10);
 Explicit Wait: Waits for a condition on a specific element.
 Syntax: WebDriverWait wait =new WebDriverWait(driver, TimeSpan.FromSeconds(10)); 
IWebElement element = wait.Until(ExpectedConditions.ElementIsVisible(By.Id("userna
me")));
2. Common Driver Methods
Navigate().GoToUrl(url) - Opens site Title - Gets title Url - Gets current URL
FindElement(By) - One element FindElements(By) - Multiple elements
Navigate().Back(), Forward(), Refresh() Manage().Window.Maximize() Close(),
Quit()
3. Handle Dropdown
SelectElement dropdown = new
SelectElement(driver.FindElement(By.Id("dropdownId")));
dropdown.SelectByText("Option 1"); dropdown.SelectByValue("value");
dropdown.SelectByIndex(2);
4. Handle Frames
driver.SwitchTo().Frame("frameName"); driver.SwitchTo().DefaultContent();
5. Return Types
FindElement() → IWebElement FindElements() → IReadOnlyCollection
6. Handle Alerts
IAlert alert = driver.SwitchTo().Alert(); alert.Accept(); alert.Dismiss(); string
text = alert.Text; alert.SendKeys("Text");
7. Multiple Windows
string parent = driver.CurrentWindowHandle; var allWindows =
driver.WindowHandles; foreach (var win in allWindows) { if (win != parent) {
driver.SwitchTo().Window(win); driver.Close(); } }
driver.SwitchTo().Window(parent);
8. Auth Popup
driver.Navigate().GoToUrl("https://username:password@yourURL.com");
9. Screenshot
ITakesScreenshot ts = (ITakesScreenshot)driver; Screenshot screenshot =
ts.GetScreenshot(); screenshot.SaveAsFile("path.png", ScreenshotImageFormat.Png);
10. Click Alternative
IJavaScriptExecutor js = (IJavaScriptExecutor)driver;
js.ExecuteScript("arguments[0].click();", element);
11. Actions Click
Actions actions = new Actions(driver);
actions.MoveToElement(element).Click().Perform();
12. Scroll
IJavaScriptExecutor js = (IJavaScriptExecutor)driver;
js.ExecuteScript("window.scrollBy(0,500);");
13. Using Statement
using OpenQA.Selenium; using (IWebDriver driver = new ChromeDriver()) {
driver.Navigate().GoToUrl("https://example.com"); }
14. Common Exceptions
StaleElementReferenceException ElementClickInterceptedException
NoSuchElementException TimeoutException
15. Try Catch
try { driver.FindElement(By.Id("btn")).Click(); } catch (Exception e) {
Console.WriteLine("Error: " + e.Message); }
16. XPath Types
Absolute: /html/body/div[1]/a Relative: //a[@id='link']
17. Axes XPath
following-sibling, preceding-sibling, parent, ancestor, descendant, child
Example: //div[@id='main']//following-sibling::p
18. Web Tables
var rows = driver.FindElements(By.XPath("//table/tbody/tr")); foreach (var row in
rows) { var cols = row.FindElements(By.TagName("td")); foreach (var col in cols)
{ Console.WriteLine(col.Text); } }
19. Serialization
Serialization: Object → Byte stream Deserialization: Byte stream → Object
